The logo for the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games is seen in Tokyo on February 15, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - The Olympic Games set to take place in Tokyo, Japan has been postponed. The showpiece has been moved to July 2021. Japan's prime minister and the head of the International Olympic Committee agreed to postpone the Tokyo 2020 Games by a year on Tuesday in an extraordinary move, unprecedented in peacetime, as the world battles the coronavirus pandemic. "I proposed to postpone for about a year and president Bach responded with 100 percent agreement," Shinzo Abe told reporters referring to Thomas Bach, head of the IOC. Additional reporting AFP